  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240&ordm;C/ 220&ordm;C (fan)/ 475&ordm;F/ Gas 9</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> wedges and pierce&nbsp;each <strong>wedge</strong> with a fork a few times, then wrap the <strong>garlic cloves</strong> (skins on) in <strong>tin foil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>pierced aubergine wedges</strong> and<strong> wrapped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>garlic cloves</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray, then put the tray in the oven and cook for 30-35 min or until the aubergine is soft and brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skins on) into wedges</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>lamb mince</strong>, <strong>panko&nbsp;breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> to a large bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix thoroughly with clean hands until fully combined, then shape into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]&nbsp;</span><strong>koftes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>red onion wedges</strong> to one half of a separate tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>lamb koftes</strong> to the other half of the tray</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15-20 min until the <strong>onions</strong> are tender and the <strong>kofte</strong> are&nbsp;browned and cooked through</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1597.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
